        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-24T13:07:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-24T13:07:00-05:00" n="232"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d232">
                <head>232. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    to the <gloss type="to">
                        <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss> Station in Guatemala</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d232fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 9, Folder 23. Secret; Operational Immediate; RYBAT;
                            <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_BRMLPE1">Bissell</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-06-24T18:07:00+00:00">June 24, 1954, 1807Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>06271. Ref: <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 4262.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d232fn2">Dated June 24. (Ibid., Box 6, Folder 4)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Considering authorization bomb Matamoros Fortress or <gloss
                            target="#t_ADAM1">Adam</gloss> petroleum storage on basis <gloss
                            target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> recommendation and previously expressed
                        views of <gloss target="#t_JMBLUG1">JMBLUG</gloss> and <gloss
                            target="#t_KUBARK1">KUBARK</gloss> reps. Wish to be sure <gloss
                            target="#t_JMBLUG1">JMBLUG</gloss> still believes bombing of selected
                        targets <gloss target="#t_ADAM1">Adam</gloss> area would be highly effective
                        as contribution to overthrow of <persName corresp="#p_AGJ1"
                            >Arbenz</persName> regime and desirable move taking into account obvious
                        political risks and current appeal by <gloss target="#t_WSBURNT1"
                            >WSBURNT</gloss> government to UN Security Council alleging threat of
                        bombing of “open cities”.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Reply Oper Immediate.</item>
                </list>
            </div>
